steps.description:
Substantive shape change. Six edit classes plus the ADR doc commit. (1) `crates/overdrive-core/src/traits/driver.rs` â€” rename `pub image: String` to `pub command: String` on `AllocationSpec`; add `pub args: Vec<String>` as the next field; doc comments on the struct migrate (the field doc on `command` reads something like `/// Host filesystem path to the binary the driver execs (e.g. "/bin/sleep"). Container drivers (Phase 2+ MicroVm/Wasm) carry their own ContentHash-typed image field on per-driver-type spec types.` and on `args` reads `/// Argv passed verbatim to the binary; the driver invokes Command::new(&self.command).args(&self.args).`). (2) `crates/overdrive-worker/src/driver.rs` â€” rewrite `build_command`'s body. The current body (`crates/overdrive-worker/src/driver.rs:131-170` per the pre-rename layout, line numbers may have drifted +/- 1 due to step 01-01) contains an `if spec.image == "/bin/cpuburn"` branch + an `if spec.image == "/bin/sleep"` / `else if spec.image == "/bin/sh"` arg-injection tree + a conditional setsid-pre-exec hook. The new body is: ```let mut cmd = Command::new(&spec.command);
        cmd.args(&spec.args);
        // SAFETY: setsid() places the spawned child in its own process group,
        // so SIGKILL on stop reaches the entire workload tree (matches the
        // pre-rename behaviour for /bin/sh-class workloads, made unconditional
        // because every exec workload deserves the same guarantee).
        unsafe { cmd.pre_exec(|| { libc::setsid(); Ok(()) }); }```. The doc comment block above `build_command` (`crates/overdrive-worker/src/driver.rs:128-145`-ish) is replaced with a new comment explaining: ExecDriver invokes the binary verbatim against the spec's argv; magic image-name dispatch was removed in 2026-04-28 per ADR-0029 amendment + ADR-0026 amendment; test fixtures construct argv inline. (3) `crates/overdrive-control-plane/src/action_shim.rs` â€” `build_phase1_restart_spec` migrates from `image: "/bin/sleep".to_string()` to `command: "/bin/sleep".to_string(), args: vec!["60".to_string()]`. (4) `crates/overdrive-core/src/reconciler.rs` â€” the one `AllocationSpec { â€¦, image: "/bin/sleep".to_string(), â€¦ }` site in `JobLifecycle::reconcile` migrates to `command: "/bin/sleep".to_string(), args: vec!["60".to_string()]`. (5) Test fixture migration â€” every `tests/integration/exec_driver/*.rs` file: replace `image: "/bin/sleep".to_owned()` with `command: "/bin/sleep".to_owned(), args: vec!["60".to_owned()]`; the `stop_escalates_to_sigkill.rs` SIGTERM-trap test replaces `image: "/bin/sh".to_owned()` (which previously triggered magic dispatch into `["-c", "trap '' TERM; sleep 60"]`) with explicit `command: "/bin/sh".to_owned(), args: vec!["-c".to_owned(), "trap '' TERM; sleep 60".to_owned()]`; the `cluster_status_under_burst.rs` cgroup-isolation test replaces `image: "/bin/cpuburn".to_string()` (which triggered busy-loop magic dispatch) with explicit `command: "/bin/sh".to_string(), args: vec!["-c".to_string(), "<the same busy-loop script as the prior magic dispatch>".to_string()]` (the exact script body comes from the pre-rename `build_command` body's cpuburn branch â€” preserve it verbatim so the test exercises the same kernel pressure); the `missing_binary.rs` test's `image: "/this/binary/does/not/exist/anywhere".to_owned()` migrates to `command: "/this/binary/does/not/exist/anywhere".to_owned(), args: vec![]`. The acceptance fixtures `sim_driver_only_in_default_lane.rs` and `sim_adapters_deterministic.rs` get `args: vec![]` added (sim driver does not exec anything; the args are inert). (6) ADR doc commit â€” stage `docs/product/architecture/adr-0026-cgroup-v2-direct-writes.md` and `docs/product/architecture/adr-0029-overdrive-worker-crate-extraction.md` (both already amended in the working tree by the architect agent; the crafter commits them alongside this code edit). Single cohesive commit. Commit message: `feat(driver): rename AllocationSpec.image â†’ command; add args; drop magic image-name dispatch (ADR-0026 + ADR-0029 amended 2026-04-28)` with `Step-ID: 01-02` trailer. Normal pre-commit hooks pass (no `--no-verify`).
